To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, we use the following formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Gross Profit = 2,861,769.51
- Total Revenue = 4,879,769.51

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{2,861,769.51}{4,879,769.51} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} \approx 58.64\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '58.64%'} }
```
